# **Graph Algorithms**

📂 **Category:** `python-programming` / `ai-ml`  
🔗 **Linked Notes:** [[alexandria-library/python-programming/python-data-structures]], [[ai-ml-overview]], [[ai-ml-neural-networks]]

## **Overview**

Graph algorithms are fundamental in **AI, machine learning, network analysis, and computational optimization**. They operate on **nodes (vertices)** connected by **edges**, forming a **graph structure**.

---

## **1️⃣ Types of Graphs**

✅ **Directed Graph (Digraph)** → Edges have direction (`A → B`)  
✅ **Undirected Graph** → Edges have no direction (`A — B`)  
✅ **Weighted Graph** → Edges have values (`A —5— B`)  
✅ **Unweighted Graph** → Edges are equal (`A — B`)  
✅ **Cyclic Graph** → Loops exist (`A → B → C → A`)  
✅ **Acyclic Graph (DAG)** → No loops (`A → B → C`)

🔗 Related: [[alexandria-library/python-programming/python-data-structures]]

---

## **2️⃣ Essential Graph Algorithms**

### **Traversal Algorithms**

🔹 **Breadth-First Search (BFS)** → Level-order exploration  
🔹 **Depth-First Search (DFS)** → Deeper exploration first

### **Shortest Path Algorithms**

🔹 **Dijkstra’s Algorithm** → Finds shortest path in weighted graphs  
🔹 __A_ (A-Star) Algorithm_* → Uses heuristics for shortest pathfinding

### **Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) Algorithms**

🔹 **Prim’s Algorithm** → Greedy algorithm for MST  
🔹 **Kruskal’s Algorithm** → Edge-based greedy approach

